# 60-Day Curriculum: Django and HTML

## Days 1-15: HTML Basics

### Day 1-3: Introduction to HTML
- Overview of HTML
- Setting up a development environment
- Basic structure of an HTML document

### Day 4-6: HTML Elements and Attributes
- Headings, paragraphs, and lists
- Links and images
- Attributes and their usage

### Day 7-9: HTML Forms
- Form tags and elements
- Input types (text, radio, checkbox, etc.)
- Form validation

### Day 10-12: HTML Tables
- Table structure and tags
- Table headers and data cells
- Styling tables with CSS

### Day 13-15: HTML Multimedia
- Embedding audio and video
- Image maps
- HTML5 canvas basics

## Days 16-45: Django Basics

### Day 16-18: Introduction to Django
- Overview of Django
- Installing Django and creating a project

### Day 19-21: Django Models
- Creating models
- Database migrations
- Admin interface

### Day 22-24: Django Views
- Understanding views
- URL patterns
- Class-based views

### Day 25-27: Django Templates
- Template syntax
- Template tags and filters
- Template inheritance

### Day 28-30: Django Forms
- Building forms
- Form validation
- Handling form submissions

### Day 31-33: Django ORM
- Querying the database
- Filters and annotations
- Aggregations

### Day 34-36: Django Static Files and Media
- Managing static files
- Handling media files
- File upload and storage

### Day 37-39: Django Middleware
- Using middleware
- Custom middleware

### Day 40-42: Django Authentication
- User authentication
- Permissions and groups
- Custom user models

## Days 43-60: Advanced Django and Project

### Day 43-45: Django Testing
- Writing tests in Django
- Test cases and fixtures
- Running tests

### Day 46-48: Version Control with Git
- Basic Git commands
- Creating branches and merging
- Collaborative development with Git

### Day 49-60: Final Project
- Planning and designing a Django project
- Implementation and troubleshooting
- Presenting and reviewing projects
